    <abstract id="aspace_f40740db0df0201d1726a2439404f9e9">Charles Keller (1914-2006) was a painter, printmaker, cartoonist and political activist. He studied printmaking at the Art Students League, NY, with Harry Sternberg and Will Barnet in the late 1930s and early 40s. Scenes of labor and portraits of the disenfranchised are prominent in his work. This collection consists of personal papers plus sketches and other original artwork from his training and career.</abstract>
